en_377172_0	Major General Shavendra Silva this morning (10) assumed office as the 53rd Chief of Staff of the Army during a simple ceremony at his office in the Army Headquarters, amid religious observances, greetings and best wishes.
en_377172_1	Soon after his arrival at the new office, he made religious offerings before members of the Maha Sangha commenced chanting to invoke blessings on the new office.
en_377172_2	While chanting was in progress, Major General Silva placed his signature in an official document to signify the acceptance of his new office.
en_377172_3	After offer of 'Pirikara' to the Maha Sangha, Senior Officers present there extended their best wishes to the new Chief of Staff.
en_377172_4	Major General Niyshshanka Ranawana, Director General General Staff, Major General Wajira Palihakkara, Director General Financial Management and several Senior Officers were present at the occasion.
en_377172_5	Here follows Major General Silva's profile: Major General Shavendra Silva WWV RWP RSP VSV USP ndc psc is currently the Adjutant General and Colonel of the Regiment, Gajaba Regiment of the Sri Lankan Army.
en_377172_6	A proud product of the Sri Lanka Military Academy, he was enlisted on 5 March 1984 to the Regular Intake 19.
en_377172_7	He has had an illustrious career from the rank of Second Lieutenant to Major General, covering all the salient appointments in his military career.
en_377172_8	Major General Silva has fulfilled all the three significant streams of any military discourse, namely an instructor, a staff officer and a Commander, which in combination is a rare fulfilment of an Officer.
en_377172_9	Major General Silva was the Ambassador and the Deputy Permanent Representative of Sri Lanka to the United Nations in New York during 2010-2015.
en_377172_10	He was the Alternative Representative of Sri Lanka to the United Nations Special Political and Decolonization Committee from 2010 to 2015.
en_377172_11	He was also the Advisor of the Sri Lankan delegation to the United Nations Social, Humanitarian and Cultural Affairs Committee.
en_377172_12	Being a Member of the Official Sri Lanka Delegation for the 66th, 67th, 68th and 69th United Nations General Assembly, Major General Silva participated in many rounds of bilateral and multilateral consultations.
en_377172_13	He also has held all Command appointments that an infantry Officer could hold ranging from that of a platoon commander to the General Officer Commanding of an Infantry Division.
en_377172_14	He has also been the Head of the Presidential Security Army Unit at the President’s House in 1987 to His Excellency, the President J.R. Jayawardena.
en_377172_15	He commanded the 58th Division and the Commando Brigade during the Humanitarian Operations and he also commanded the 53rd Division which is the Reserve Strike Force and also commanded the Air Mobile Brigade.
en_377172_16	Major General Silva commanded three Infantry Battalions during the crucial period of the Sri Lankan Military.
en_377172_17	He had held key staff appointments in the Military Secretary's Branch, the Directorate of Plans, the Directorate of Training and as the Staff officer to the Security Force Headquarters, Jaffna.
en_377172_18	Soon after the Humanitarian Operation was over in the year 2009, he was appointed as the Director General Operations at the Army Headquarters & also was appointed as Colonel Commandant of the Commando Regiment.
en_377172_19	Major General Silva in his instructional capacity was the Commanding Officer of the Sri Lanka Military Academy.
en_377172_20	Prior to that, during his young officer days, he had been a Course Officer to the Officer Cadet Intake 37 which included the first foreign Officer Cadet student batch, trained by the Sri Lanka Army.
en_377172_21	Major General Shavendra Silva is one of the highest decorated military officers with different varieties of medals and he was the first Second Lieutenant of the Sri Lanka Army to receive three different types of gallantry medals, namely WWV, RWP, RSP for the first time.
en_377172_22	He has been skillfully trained in diverse fields in the USA, Israel, Netherlands, Greece, Italy, France, Pakistan and India.
en_377172_23	He is a graduate from the Harvard University in the United States and holds an MSc in Philosophy and in Defence and Strategic Studies in India.
en_377172_24	He has been trained and qualified in psychological operations by the United States Army.
en_377172_25	He is a graduate of the Defence Services Command and Staff College and holds a Diploma in personnel management.
en_377172_26	He is also an instructor to the International Humanitarian Law Course and a qualified physical training instructor.
en_377172_27	Major General Shavendra Silva is an author of the proclaimed book, titled "Sri Lankan Identity since 2600 years", which was written to mark the 2600th Anniversary of the Buddha's Enlightenment.
en_377172_28	In appreciation of his service, rendered to the nation, Major General Shavendra Silva was also awarded the “Sri Lankeshwara Aparadha Meheyum Visharadha Jothikadhaja Veeraparthapa Deshamanya Jathika Gourawanama Sammana Upadhi Sannas Pathraya”, and the “Veera Gajendra Sangramasuri Jathika Gourawanama Sannaspathraya” & “ Weerawickrama Deshabhani Wishwa Keerthi Sri Ranashura” (the most prestigious awards that a lay-person can receive) by all three sects of the Sri Lankan Buddhist order for true devotion to preserve the sovereignty and the territorial integrity of the motherland.
en_377172_29	Further, he was recently named and honoured as the “Mederata Abhimanaya” (Pride of the Upcountry) by eminent personalities in the central hill country of Sri Lanka.
en_377172_30	Major General Shavendra Silva is the Chairman of the Defence Services Hockey Committee & Army Hockey Committee & a proud old boy of St Thomas College, Matale.
